init_text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You see a tiny bee, no bigger than a thumb, sitting on your shoulder.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Don't worry, your majesty, I'm not going to sting you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are still a little apprehensive, but you ask the bee what he can do to help you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You ask the bee what the truth is, and he says "You are the last of the royal family, and you are a bee

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are shocked, and ask the bee if he is sure.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You ask the bee what you should do, and he says "You must go to the humans and ask them to stop eating all of

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You go to the humans and ask them to stop eating all the honey.
